         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>māka</w><w>pñi</w><w>nauṣ</w><w>yāmuwa</w><w>saṃsārne</w><w>kleśanma</w>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>krä</supplied>tātñi</w><w>ṣp</w><w>onolmi</w><w>ṣnoma-näkṣiṃ</w>
<w>kärtse<lb corresp="#a3"/><supplied>ritāñ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>kä</supplied>stwer</w><pc>:</pc><w>tān</w><w>ot</w><w>yolyyai</w><w>preśyaine</w>
<w>lä<lb corresp="#a4"/><supplied>klenta</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/><w>darinne</w><pc>॥</pc></p>
            <lg type="poem" met="frg:M21_21_18_13" subtype="hom">
               <lg n="1" type="strophe">
                  <l n="b" real="7/4"><w>paṣ</w><w>snai</w><w>nerke</w><w>saṃsārne</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>po</w>
<lb corresp="#a5"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>cy</w><w>ompostäṃ</w><pc>:</pc></l>
                  <l n="d" real="7/2"><w>po</w><w>ñatsenta</w><w>wīkäskau-c</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>yāmtsi</w><pc>:</pc></l>
               </lg>
               <lg n="2" type="strophe">
                  <l n="b" real="7/4/4"><w>ṣeme</w><w>rano</w><w>kṣaṇaṣṣe</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>totka</w>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>ysomo</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>cīsa</w><w>tattau</w><pc>:</pc></l>
                  <l n="d" real="7/8/4"><w>kwri</w><w>no</w><w>śamtar</w>
<w>te<lb corresp="#b3"/><supplied>lkine</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w><supplied>pañäk</supplied>täñeṣṣe</w><w>akālkäś</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>prakreṃ</w><w>palsko</w><pc>:</pc><num value="2">2</num></l>
               </lg>
               <lg n="3" type="strophe">
                  <l n="a">
<lb corresp="#b4"/><gap reason="lost"/></l>
                  <l n="c" real="7/5"><w>ñ<supplied>i</supplied>ś</w><w>mātärsa</w><w>wawāyau</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>präthagjaññe</w>
<lb corresp="#b5"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>c</w><pc>:</pc></l>
                  <l n="d" real="7/5"><w>karunmeṃ</w><w>no</w><w>poyśiṃñe</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>källālle</w>
<w>ke<lb/><supplied>ktseñ</supplied></w></l>
               </lg>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having previously done much merit, ... the passions in the saṃsāra ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... and the grateful beings destroying the decay (?) [and] (seeking) the good ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... by night. Then in this evil time the sufferings ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in the tune ... Go without delay in the saṃsāra, all ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... following you. I will chase away all distresses. </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in order to do. Even the small (period) of a single instant ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... totally I will stand by you. But if you go (to the sacrifice?) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the firm mind towards the wish of Buddha rank. </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... I guided by the mother, ... the profane state ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... you (?). But out of compassion I shall obtain the body of the omniscient ...      </seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">This fragment may belong to the same manuscript as <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-pkns56"/>. It is the right part of a leaf including the right margin. It shows traces of horizontal and vertical ruling.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">The form <hi>ṣnoma</hi> which is here a first member of a verbal governing compound with <hi>-näkṣi</hi> as a second member is also attested in <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht1392i"/> a2 in the form <hi>ṣnom</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment">The metrical passage seems to follow a type of 4x18 syllables with a rhythm of 7/7/4.</note></p>
         </div>
